rComments: Randomly started adding 1 question quizzes at the end of his classes with no warning for other students that couldn't be there. Does not give you clear instructions on your group project (especially the survey), just says you're doing it wrong. He's the toughest grader I've ever had in my 3 years of uni here, he makes me wanna drop out so bad

This prof has zero respect for his students, he will absolutely attack you during final presentations and you have to sit there and take it. His instructions for the group presentation are so unclear, he can't practice what he preaches either. Save your time; take this course in English or something cuz he will demolish your spirit and confidence.

Midterm is easy. Very few instructions for projects but he has high expectations. He said insanely rude comments to people about their presentations in front of the whole class. Would not recommend this class if you respect yourself.

While he mainly reads his powerpoint with his stupid bird chirping in the background, he expects so much but doesn't tell you what he wants. The group project is so unclear it hurts. He tells you what he what to do but doesn't explain how and what he expects. Then insults you in front of the whole class. He's degrading but the midterms were easy.

He's almost always late to his class and he seems to read the power point as he presents it (not prepared). His class have a important lack of dynamism, but he gives good examples. If your looking for a class where you can only read the power point to pass, it's great, but if you need motivation and dynamisme, that's not the one.

Overall a very lazy prof. He puts no effort in his teaching making the classes super boring. The midterms were super easy and the group project was graded pretty subjectively. The final was so hard it was like nothing we had ever seen in the course. Dont take this prof.
Nice lectures, but i feel like the professor does not want people to pass
